<div style="font-size:45px"><center>≼ "Late Night Radio" ≽</center></div>
---------

Being in Team R-1 of the [[M.E.G]] is always a thankless job, and it certainly doesn't help when you're on radio duty for the thousandth time. Whenever they can't find new stuff in the Backrooms to send explorers to their death for, they always put a couple unlucky saps like you in front of a radio and a Level Key, telling you to predict level properties from the sounds in the radio like you're a fucking fortune teller.

You always have to bring a bunch of [[Object 1|Almond Water]] for the occasion too, since the damn thing is cognitohazardous too. It's practically an open secret around these parts that after discovering this frequency bullshit, Judah Casper fucking pulled a Ronnie Mcnutt on himself after almost getting his brain fried by [[Phenomenon 35|Roth Syndrome]]. Heard his rotting body's still laying around in a [[Base Alpha]] storage room.

Thankfully, your shift's finally about to end. The bullshit you wrote in your Terminal about the audio isn't useful, but it's probably enough to get your paycheck. Just before checking out for the day, you decide to go browsing BACK-NET for a bit; it's not like you have much else to do. Clicking on the random site button, you're shocked to find what comes up on the screen.

"backnet9223372036854775807://memories.lim". The page hasn't loaded yet since the latency means it's probably gonna take forever to even access the site, but the fact that this site wasn't entirely a dead link implies that this site is hosted exactly on Level 9223372036854775807; unimaginably far from any explored level. If the Backrooms are really that big, massive enough for hundreds of thousands of years of humanity to have barely scratched the surface, what does that mean for this place? What does that mean for us?

Opening your Backmail up, you began to write one final report. This was going to be a very interesting night.
